  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol in Envoy is implemented through a layered architecture with both legacy and unified implementations. At the highest level, the GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h and .cc) serves as the entry point, with separate factories for State-of-the-World (SotW) and Delta subscription modes. The factory instantiates GrpcSubscriptionImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h and .cc), which acts as an adapter from the typed Subscription interface to the untyped GrpcMux interface.\n\nFor the legacy implementations, GrpcMuxImpl in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/ implements the SotW protocol, while NewGrpcMuxImpl in the same directory implements the Delta protocol. Both handle the gRPC stream management and message multiplexing.\n\nThe unified XdsMux implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h and .cc) introduces a template-based design with GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS> as the base template, parameterized by subscription state type (S), factory type (F), request type (RQ), and response type (RS). This template is instantiated as two concrete classes: GrpcMuxSotw for State-of-the-World protocol and GrpcMuxDelta for Delta protocol. Both variants support the same GrpcMux interface but differ in their protocol state management.\n\nThe subscription state management is delegated to specialized classes: SotwSubscriptionState (xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h and .cc) for SotW protocol and DeltaSubscriptionState (xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h and .cc) for Delta protocol. These inherit from BaseSubscriptionState (xds_mux/subscription_state.h), a template base class parameterized by response and request types. Each subscription state type has a corresponding factory (SotwSubscriptionStateFactory and DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory) implementing the SubscriptionStateFactory<T> template interface.\n\nThe legacy DeltaSubscriptionState implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h and .cc) provides the original Delta protocol logic before the unified template design was introduced. The factory implementation in grpc_subscription_factory.cc conditionally selects between unified and legacy implementations using the runtime feature flag 'envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux'."
}

